1. Always use best software engineering practises.
    - Do not use duplicated code
    - Use modular or OOP as needed
    - Add separate files/folders by abstracting things where necessary
    - Keep things simple
2. Maintain a scratchpad and keep it up to date on planning and execution. Update it with what works what failed
3. When fixing something, think through a few solutions and propose a couple of most likely ones before applying the solution
4. Make the code easy to read and extend
5. Keep the code as short as possible.
6. Do not code before thinking through or discussing your approach with the user